abstract: Conservative activists say House Republicans will likely begin last attempt of 2015 to cut off federal money for Planned Parenthood, but it will most likely be last such effort until GOP wins presidency.
lead_paragraph: After five years of fruitless legislative attacks, a House vote next week is likely to be the last, conservative activists say, until a Republican moves into the White House.

headline.main: Break Is Likely in Planned Parenthood Funding Battle
